'''Affiong Williams''' is a Nigerian entrepreneur from [[Akwa Ibom]] State. She is the founder and CEO of ''Reel Fruit'', a Nigerian company that processes and distributes locally grown fruits. She is married to '''Tayo Oviosu''', the CEO of the finance company Paga.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://reelfruit.com/about-us/|title=About Us {{!}} Reelfruit|work=Reelfruit|access-date=2018-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref>
== Education == Williams is a graduate in physiology and psychology from the [[University of Witwatersrand]], [[South Africa]]. She also holds a postgraduate diploma in business management from the same university.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Anudu |first1=Odinaka |title=How Affiong Williams brought Reelfruit to limelight |url=https://www.businessdayonline.com/life-arts/enterpreneur/article/affiong-williams-brought-reelfruit-limelight/ |accessdate=15 July 2018 |publisher=Business Day (online) |date=15 January 2018}}</ref> She also attended the [[Stanford Graduate School of Business]] where she took part in the Seed Transformation Program of 2018.
== Career == After her postgraduate diploma, she worked with Endeavour South Africa from 2008 to 2012 where she rose to the position of Portfolio Manager.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globalbusinessforum.com/africa/speakers/92|title=Affiong Williams {{!}} Africa 2017 {{!}} Global Business Forum|website=globalbusinessforum.com|language=en|access-date=2018-07-17}}</ref> She returned to Nigeria in 2012 and started off ReelFruit, her own agribusiness.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Essiet |first1=Daniel |title=Her road to success |url=http://thenationonlineng.net/road-success-2/ |accessdate=16 July 2018 |agency=The Nation |issue=7 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://womenofrubies.com/profile-meet-affiong-williams-the-young-lady-introducing-a-new-snack-into-the-nigerian-market/|title=#PROFILE{{!}} MEET AFFIONG WILLIAMS, THE YOUNG LADY INTRODUCING A NEW SNACK INTO THE NIGERIAN MARKET|last=Ijewere|first=Esther|work=Women of Rubies|access-date=2018-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref> She is said to have started the company in her apartment in [[Surulere]], with an initial savings of $8,000.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Adekoya |first1=Femi |title=Affiong Williams: Low consumer purchasing power affecting businesses |url=https://guardian.ng/business-services/affiong-williams/amp/ |accessdate=16 July 2018 |agency=The Guardian (Nigeria) |date=17 March 2017}}</ref>
== Personal life == She is married to Tayo Oviosu, the founder and CEO of the finance company Paga.<Ref>[https://mypaga.com/ Paga]</ref>
== Awards and recognitions == She was listed by [[Forbes]] among the ''Africa's Most Promising Entrepreneurs'' in 2015. ReelFruit won an international Women In Business Competition in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dolan |first1=Kerry A. |title=Africa's Most Promising Young Entrepreneurs: Forbes Africa's 30 Under 30 For 2015 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kerryadolan/2015/06/12/africas-most-promising-young-entrepreneurs-forbes-africas-30-under-30-for-2015/amp/ |accessdate=15 July 2018 |agency=Forbes |date=13 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Onehi |first1=Victoria |title=Affiong Williams Makes Forbes Africa's Billionaire List |url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/news/women-enterpreneurs/affiong-williams-makes-forbes-africa-s-billionaires-list/155376.html |accessdate=16 July 2018 |publisher=Daily Trust |date=14 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Essiet |first1=Daniel |title=Her road to success |url=http://thenationonlineng.net/road-success-2/ |accessdate=16 July 2018 |agency=The Nation |issue=7 January 2015}}</ref>
