In January 2017, the company was acquired by [[Wix.com]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/01/19/wix-buys-flok-to-add-loyalty-and-mobile-crm-to-its-suite-of-business-tools/|title=Wix buys Flok to add loyalty and mobile CRM to its business tools|last=Lunden|first=Ingrid|date=19 January 2017|website=[[TechCrunch]]|publisher=|access-date=23 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.globes.co.il/en/article-wix-acquires-israeli-crm-co-flok-1001173124|title=Wix acquires Israeli CRM co flok - Globes|website=Globes|language=he|access-date=2018-06-07}}</ref>
==Background== flok was founded in 2011 by Ido Gaver and Eran Kirshenboim and has offices in [[Tel Aviv]], [[Israel]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zimmerman|first1=Eilene|title=LoyalBlocks Simplifies Mobile App Creation for Small Merchants|url=http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/16/loyalblocks-simplifies-mobile-app-creation-for-small-merchants/?_r=1|accessdate=26 July 2016|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> In May 2013, flok secured a $9 million Series A Round from [[General Catalyst Partners]] with participation from Founder Collective and existing investor Gemini Israel Ventures.<ref>https://thenextweb.com/insider/2013/05/23/nyc-based-loyalblocks-raises-9m-for-its-automated-mobile-loyalty-program/#gref</ref> In total, flok has raised over $18 million in [[venture capital]] in three rounds.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Taylor|first1=Colleen|title=LoyalBlocks Lands $9 Million Led By General Catalyst To Scale Out Its Mobile-Based Loyalty Program|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/05/23/loyalblocks-9-million-funding/|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Flok company profile on CrunchBase|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/loyalblocks#/entity|publisher=[[CrunchBase]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Your next loyalty ‘punch card’ will be driven by AI|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/04/07/your-next-loyalty-punch-card-will-be-driven-by-ai|publisher=[[VentureBeat]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref>
In May 2014, flok announced a self-service loyalty platform for SMBs to build their own programs with beacon integration. At that time, approximately 40,000 businesses were using the service.<ref>http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/225373/loyalblocks-adds-beacon-to-self-serve-loyalty-plat.html</ref> In 2016, flok released a turnkey chatbot service for local businesses,<ref>https://venturebeat.com/2016/07/26/flok-uses-bluetooth-and-chatbots-to-lure-people-inside-thousands-of-small-businesses/</ref><ref>http://marketingland.com/flok-wants-bring-chatbots-small-business-masses-186056</ref> and was featured in [[AdWeek]] for developing the first "weed bot" chatbot for a [[California]] [[cannabis]] business.<ref>{{cite web|title=This California Marijuana Dispensary Is Using Bots to Understand Customers' Preferences|url=http://www.adweek.com/news/technology/california-marijuana-dispensary-using-bots-understand-customers-preferences-172238|publisher=[[Adweek]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref>
